member.remarks:
User configurable base matrix. (like as rotate, translate, ...) 

ToResult = matries at stack * BaseMatrix. 

User can use IRtc2ndHead.CtlHeadOffset instead. 

Default : Matrix4x4.Identity 



Not allowed operations :

 Matrix4x4.CreateScale with negative factor.




// If scan-head has rotated 90 deg
BaseMatrix = Matrix4x4.CreateRotationZ((float)(90 * Math.PI / 180.0));
// If scan-head has rotated 90 deg and translate dx 10mm
BaseMatrix = Matrix4x4.CreateRotationZ((float)(90 * Math.PI / 180.0)) * Matrix4x4.CreateTranslation(10, 0, 0));
// If scan-head scale up to 10%
BaseMatrix = Matrix4x4.CreateScale(1.1f);
// Reset 
BaseMatrix = Matrix4x4.Identity;

member.summary:
Push matrix into stack at top

float radius = 10;
float width = 10;
float height = 5;
rtc.ListBegin();
for (float angle = 0; angle < 360; angle += 10)
{
    var radian = angle * Math.PI / 180.0;
    rtc.MatrixStack.Push(Matrix4x4.CreateTranslation(radius, 0, 0)); // 2. translate
    rtc.MatrixStack.Push(Matrix4x4.CreateRotationZ((float)radian)); // 1. rotate
    rtc.ListJumpTo(new Vector2(-width / 2, height / 2));
    rtc.ListMarkTo(new Vector2(width / 2, height / 2));
    rtc.ListMarkTo(new Vector2(width / 2, -height / 2));
    rtc.ListMarkTo(new Vector2(-width / 2, -height / 2));
    rtc.ListMarkTo(new Vector2(-width / 2, height / 2));
    rtc.MatrixStack.Pop(); // 1. rotate
    rtc.MatrixStack.Pop(); // 2. translate
}
rtc.ListEnd();
rtc.ListExecute(true);


Not allowed operations : 

 Matrix4x4.CreateScale with negative factor.

